cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses security issues in Named Data Networking (NDN), which is a networking architecture that aims to move the Internet towards a content distribution model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security problems and proposes solutions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, since NDN involves data centers and content distribution, it could also be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, since the paper discusses security issues, it could also be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
